===Etymology===
{{PIE root|nl|kerp}}
From {{inh|nl|odt|*hervist}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*harbistaz}}, from {{der|nl|ine-pro|*kerp-}}. Cognate with High German {{m|de|Herbst}}, Low German {{m|nds|Harvst}}, West Frisian {{m|fy|hjerst}}, English {{m|en|harvest}}; further with Latin {{m|la|carpere||to [[pick]], to [[pluck]]}}, Greek {{m|grc|καρπός||fruit, harvest}}. The original meaning was ‘harvest time’, as is seen in {{m|nl|herfstmaand}}.

